Description: Condition: Excellent - very clean with little signs of wear! The Club King 290 is a great blues/rock option that delivers the acoustic overtones of a full hollow body, with even more clarity. It's loaded with CP90 pickups in the neck and bridge, delivering raw edge and rich tones. The back, sides and center block are produced from one slab of korina which is routed from the top, and then capped with a solid spruce top. The bolt-on roasted maple neck features a comfortable medium oval profile, with 12" fingerboard radius and 22 medium frets.  Features & Technical Specs: Body Wood: Semi-hollow korina, solid spruce top Body Color/Finish: Midnight Black Neck Wood: Roasted maple, satin amber finish Neck Profile: Medium oval Neck Radius: 12" Neck Joint: Bolt-on Fingerboard: Blackwood Fingerboard Inlays: Dots Frets: 22 medium jumbo Nut: Boneite Nut Width: 1-11/16" (43mm) Tuners: Reverend pin-lock Scale Length: 25-1/2" Bridge: Bigsby B-50 with Roller Bridge Pickups: CP90 Bridge, CP90 Neck Controls: Volume, tone, bass contour, 3-way Switching: 3-Way Pickup Switch: P1 - Bridge Pickup P2 - Bridge and Neck Pickup P3 - Neck Pickup Hardware Finish: Chrome Weight: 8.02 lbs.
